The alphabets shifted 13 letters which is ROT13 encryption.
Since alphabet is 13 letters that means 13 letters shifted twice would you get you the OG script.
I tried doing tr data.txt, but it didn't work.
Use cat data.txt with the piping instead to transfer the output of cat to the input of tr
tr requires two strings to decode the ROT13
the two strings are 'A-Za-z' and 'N-ZA-Mn-za-m'
The reason you DONT do 'N-Mn-m' is because the computer can't tell you wrapped around the alphabet.
So you have to include two chunks of the alphabet so it can figure it out.
So N to M would require the first chunk of alphabet to be in front of the N-Z as it indicates you wrapped around into the next set of alphabet.
